comments: Ayton (PHX) jumps from point A to point B and makes contact with Nurkic (POR) that affects his play at the basket.
Paul (PHX) rests his forearm on Lillard (POR) as he releases the pass and falls out of bounds.
Payne (PHX) makes contact with Powell's (POR) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Covington (POR) makes incidental "high-five" contact with Payne (PHX) after the release that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Crowder (PHX) makes incidental contact with Lillard's (POR) midsection after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
Bridges (PHX) makes incidental foot to foot contact with his teammate Johnson (PHX) and falls off-ball.
Ayton (PHX) pushes Nurkic (POR) in the back and affects his ability to get to the rebound.
Replay review of the jump ball pursuant to a coach?s challenge was deemed unsuccessful.  A jump ball would stand.
Paul (PHX) commits a take foul on Powell (POR).
Paul (PHX) releases his off forearm and makes marginal contact with Covington (POR) during his step back as he begins his shot attempt.
Crowder (PHX) places a forearm to the front of Lillard (POR) that affects his SQBR and dislodges the ball.
Covington (POR) makes marginal contact with Ayton's (PHX) arm after the release that does not affect his shot near the rim.
Ayton (PHX) makes marginal contact to Powell's (POR) body prior to deflecting the ball on the driving shot attempt.
Nurkic (POR) establishes his screening position in Crowder's (PHX) path and absorbs the side to side contact.
Crowder (PHX) commits a take foul on Lillard (POR).
Johnson (PHX) commits a take foul on Lillard (POR).
Crowder (PHX) enters the lane prior to Lillard (POR) releasing his free throw attempt.
Covington's  (POR) makes marginal contact to Paul's (PHX) front as he turns and faces during the trap.
Powell (POR) extends his knee forward and makes contact to Payne's (PHX) lower body and affects his SQBR.
